e makers of Victorian Britain. This book, based on AHRC-funded research, outlines the achievements of these remarkable siblings and uncovers the histories of some of the 36 unknown artisan employees that worked alongside them. Dalziel Brothers made works of global importance: illustrations to Lewis Carroll’s Alice books, novels by Charles Dickens, and landmark Pre-Raphaelite prints, as well as other, brilliant works that are published here for the first time since their initial creation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2021. 7aDESIGN / Graphic Arts / Illustration.2bisacsh  aAlice in Wonderland.  aCharles Dickens.  aDalziel Brothers.  amass media illustration.  aprint techniques.  atechnicians' authorship.  auser-generated archives.  avisual memoir.  awood engraving medium.  aword-image theory.1 aStevens, Bethan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615667940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526156679423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526156679/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packageb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles